President Muhammadu Buhari yesterday sent a message of solidarity to Prime Minister Boris Johnson of the United Kingdom. Buhari, in a statement yesterday by his media aide, Garba Shehu, prayed that Johnson get well soon enough to resume great leadership of his country at this most trying time in global history. “On behalf of the government and people of Nigeria, President Buhari wishes Prime Minister Johnson a quick recovery and restoration to full health. “President Buhari’s sympathy and solidarity are with the British leader as he battles COVID-19 personally, and with the British people as their country battles the devastating effects of the pandemic,” the President also said in the statement. Johnson was moved to the Intensive Care Unit at St Thomas’ Hospital, London, Monday night after his condition worsened because of persistent symptoms of the pandemic COVID-19. COVID-19: Buhari sends message of solidarity to PM Boris Johnson COVID-19: Ministers donate 50% of March salaries As Nigeria records 3rd Covid-19 case: FG bans officials from foreign trips